        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>&#34;The Hesperus&#34;¬ù<lb/>
                Magnolia&#44;<lb/>
                Mass.<lb/>
                July 13<hi rend="sup">th</hi> &#91;18&#93;84<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Mr. Morais&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>Charles has written<lb/> me concerning the project of your Italian<lb/> friend with regard to our honored co&#45;<lb/>religionist Sir Moses Montefiore.<lb/></p>
            <p>The idea of presenting an album seems<lb/> excellent&#44; and if the lines addressed<lb/> to Sir Moses by me last autumn will<lb/> be acceptable&#44; I shall be happy to<lb/> give them as my contribution. I<lb/> should prefer this to writing fresh matter&#44;<lb/> as I could only repeat myself&#44; either in<lb/> prose or verse.<lb/></p>
            <p>Charles may be out of town this week&#44;<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>and therefore asked me to send my<lb/> reply direct to you.<lb/></p>
            <p>If my decision meets your views&#44;<lb/> and you will send me &#94; here the particular<lb/> sheet of paper which Charles tells<lb/> me is required&#44; I will copy the lines<lb/> on it and return the same to you.<lb/></p>
            <p>With love to Nina&#44; and kind<lb/> regards to yourself and household&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>Sincerely yours&#44;
                Mary M. Cohen<lb/></p>
                
            <p>Mother and Kate desire to be specially<lb/>remembered to you all. We shall<lb/> be here until August 1st&#58; after that&#44;<lb/> my address will be<lb/></p>
            <p><hi rend="underline">Maplewood Cottage</hi><lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">Maplewood</hi>&#44;<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">New Hampshire</hi>.<lb/></p>
        </body>
    </text>
